daily_routine: Every morning at 5 AM, Esperanza would walk the same forest paths her
  grandmother taught her, checking the oyamel fir trees for butterfly clusters. She'd
  prepare traditional hot chocolate with cinnamon for tourists, sharing stories in
  three languages about how her great-grandmother could predict the monarchs' arrival
  by the angle of morning light through the canopy. Now she walks empty trails, the
  silence broken only by chainsaws clearing land for more avocado trees.
