significant_object: A hand-carved wooden monarch butterfly made by her grandmother,
  painted with natural pigments. It was traditionally passed to the next generation
  when the butterflies returned each November. Now it sits unused on her kitchen table
  - there's no one left to receive it, and no butterflies to mark the season.
