vulnerability_details: Like monarchs whose multi-generational migration was broken
  when climate disrupted timing, Esperanza's family's four-generation tradition of
  guiding monarch tourism ended when the butterflies stopped arriving. Her grandmother's
  indigenous Purépecha knowledge of seasonal timing became useless when spring arrived
  six weeks early three years running.
